question: Question: The nebkha and parabolic types of these objects usually form near vegetation. For 10 points each: [10] Name these objects of which the crescent-shaped type, known as barchans, is the most abundant on Earth as well as Mars. These objects form via aeolian processes and are a very common feature of deserts.
